cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SC, cs.FL. 

The paper deals with proving termination of rewrite systems, which is a topic in both logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of (pseudo-)propositional logic to encode constraints suggests a connection to automated reasoning and SAT solving (cs.DS, cs.SC). Finally, the Knuth-Bendix order is a well-known concept in formal language theory (cs.FL).
